 Job Description
 
As a member of the Corporate team, you will be a part of the backbone of a company that builds and brings to market artificial intelligence technologies, including natural language processing and cognitive computing. You will build best practices that will serve internal (and sometimes external) customers and business partners.
 
The Graphic Designer role will work closely with Senior Designer and Creative Director to support all Marketing and company-wide collateral and event design as well as PPT presentations. Help propel the Interactions brand with consistent design and messaging through various channels including digital and print.
 
Refine PPT slide graphics and visual story for Sales, Marketing, Technology and HR that clearly demonstrate capabilities of Interactions solutions. Use layout and composition skills to rearrange information and ‚Äútell a better visual story‚Äù. Make sure final presentations are following brand standards. Produce custom imagery and icons for slides as necessary.
 
Produce visually compelling final pieces using templates for ebooks, whitepapers, research surveys, and various content related graphics. Contribute your own composition and layout skills to enhance the visual communication of these pieces.
 
Work with designers, content writers, marketing, technology and HR to understand unique project requirements. Help translate requirements and outcomes into impactful design.
 
Produce various web graphics for our Resource Center postings and other areas of the website as needed.
 
 Requirements: 
Must have a minimum of 4+ years of related experience.
 
Proficient in PowerPoint, Microsoft Office PPT and Google Slides.
 
Solid experience with Master slides and templates.
 
Solid experience with PPT and Google Slides tools including (but not limited to) shapes/fonts/smart art, choosing color and styles, cleaning up fonts, charts, graphs, animation tools, etc.
 
Great aesthetic eye for consistency and style guidelines.
 
Ability to work under tight deadlines, multitask and quick turnaround.
 
Ability to take information and transform it into compelling story telling using your own layout and composition skills that follow design best practices.
 
 
 Design and Production 
 
 Solid experience with Adobe Creative Suite software:  Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign.
 
Solid experience with web and print graphics production and appropriate resolutions.
 
Working with Photoshop templates as well as building graphics from start to finish without a template to create final design pieces for our Resource Center (Blog, Events Announcements, Video postings). Solid experience with layering different photos and graphics to create stellar imagery.
 
Working with InDesign templates as well as creating new templates to create white papers, eBooks, case studies.
 
Working with Illustrator to create various file formats of Interactions logo, edit and format our custom icons, create new icons, assist in prepping graphics/logo for partners/investors for web and internal use.
 
Experience with image searching and choosing appropriate images that enhance content.
 
 Preferred: 
Web User Experience Design a plus.
 
Animation skills and knowledge of Adobe After Effects a plus.
 
Illustration skills a plus.
 
